r, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mac","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Cuong, Minh, Lien, Muoi, Thanh, Tho, Tieu, Vinh, Anh, Beo, Binh, Chau.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surnames 麥 (see   Mai   2) and 莫 (see   Mo   1).","Vietnamese (<b>Mạc</b>): from Chinese 莫 ‘nothing; nonexistent’; see   Mo   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Mai","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Thanh, Hoa, Son, Dung, Long, Binh, Minh, Thu, Hue, Huong, Thuy.  Chinese Chi, Hong, Ho, Sang, Han, Hang, Jian, Li, Man, Mei, Sen, Wei.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 麥, meaning ‘wheat’ in Chinese: (i) from Mai Qiu (麥丘), the title of a man in the state of Qi (located mainly in present-day Shandong province) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), who, despite being very old, came to celebrate the birthday of the Duke Huan of Qi (ruler of the state of Qi, died 643  BC ). His descendants inherited 麥, the first part of his title, as their surname. (ii) borne by descendants of Mai Tie Zhang (麥鐵杖), a famous general during the Sui dynasty (581–618  AD ). His descendants were scattered around southern China.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 買, meaning ‘buy’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of the king Song Weizi, founder of the state of Song. (ii) borne by descendants of the Duke Dao of Xu (ruler of the state of Xu, 546–523  BC ), possibly inheriting his personal name. (iii) from the first element of the personal name Mai Zhu Chu (買朱鉏), style name of an official who lived during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iv) it has also been traced back to other ethnic groups in northern China."]}]},{"name":"Dufagan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Donegan  . This form of the surname is rare in Ireland and Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Donegan","meanings":["Dona, unhappy, and gan, offspring, signifying and unhappy child"]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Dufagan Mac Indreachtaich 1st was born in 1090, in Scotland, his father, Aed Heth I Mormaer Of Moray, was 40 and his mother, Tul or Orlin MacDuff, Princess of Scotland, was 32. He married Fynuella Mearns about 1117, in Forfar, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He was buried in Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1090–1118":"1090–1118","1080–Male":"1080–Surnud","1089–1139":"1089–1139","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1095–1118":"1095–1118","1095–1130":"1095–1130","1097–1168":"1097–1168","1097–1136":"1097–1136","1100–1201":"1100–1201","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1050–1116":"1050–1116","1058–1097":"1058–1097","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","Abt 1117":"umbes 1117","1187":"1187","1097":"1097","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1050":"1050","1118":"1118","1139":"1139","1116":"1116","1136":"1136","1058":"1058","1201":"1201","1168":"1168","1100":"1100","1089":"1089","about 1097":"umbes 1097","Methil, Fife, Scotland":"Methil, Fife, Scotland","Forfarshire, Angushire, Scotland":"Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Forfar, Angusshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1090–1118":"1090–1118","1080–Male":"1080–Kuollut","1089–1139":"1089–1139","1090–Female":"1090–Kuollut","1095–1118":"1095–1118","1095–1130":"1095–1130","1097–1168":"1097–1168","1097–1136":"1097–1136","1100–1201":"1100–1201","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1050–1116":"1050–1116","1058–1097":"1058–1097","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","Abt 1117":"noin 1117","1187":"1187","1097":"1097","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1050":"1050","1118":"1118","1139":"1139","1116":"1116","1136":"1136","1058":"1058","1201":"1201","1168":"1168","1100":"1100","1089":"1089","about 1097":"noin 1097","Methil, Fife, Scotland":"Methil, Fife, Scotland","Forfarshire, Angushire, Scotland":